The paper deals with the geometric problem of representing semantically related words in a word cloud, which involves designing efficient algorithms for contact between rectangles. This problem falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS) as it involves designing algorithms for geometric objects. Additionally, the paper deals with semantic relatedness, which is a key concept in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing and text analysis, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
